-- Fiat says investment in Melfi plant equally divided with Chrysler
-- 
-- Tue Apr 9, 2013 7:10am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/04/09/us-fiat-melfi-idUSBRE9380B520130409

 

 TURIN  (Reuters) - Fiat ( FIA.MI ) Chief Executive Sergio Marchionne said on Tuesday that the investment to build Jeeps at its Melfi plant is shared with U.S. unit Chrysler. 
 "The investments forecast for Melfi of over a billion euros will be equally divided between Fiat and Chrysler," Marchionne said at a shareholders' meeting. Fiat owns 58.5 percent of Chrysler. (Reporting by Jennifer Clark, editing by Silvia Aloisi)